# Data Mining Assignment 3

## Downloading the Dataset

To complete this assignment, you need to download the `twitter_combined.txt.gz` dataset from the Stanford Network Analysis Project (SNAP) and place it in the `data` folder.

### Steps to Download the Dataset

1. Open your terminal or web browser.
2. Download the dataset using the following link:
    [twitter_combined.txt.gz](https://snap.stanford.edu/data/twitter_combined.txt.gz)
3. Once downloaded, move the file to the `data` folder in this project directory.

### Command Line Instructions

Alternatively, you can use the following command to download and move the file directly:
```bash
wget https://snap.stanford.edu/data/twitter_combined.txt.gz -P data/
```

## Setting Up the Environment

Ensure you are using Python 3.1.x for this assignment. You can install the required dependencies by running:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```